class MyModel(nn.Module):
  def __init__(self):
    super().__init__()
    self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(3, 64, kernel_size=3, stride=1, padding=1)
    self.bn1 = nn.BatchNorm2d(64)
    self.relu = nn.ReLU(inplace=True)

    self.conv_blocks = nn.ModuleList([
        self._make_conv_block(64, 64),
        self._make_conv_block(64, 64),
        self._make_conv_block(64, 64),
        self._make_conv_block(64, 64),
        self._make_conv_block(64, 96),
        self._make_conv_block(96, 96),
        self._make_conv_block(96, 96),
        self._make_conv_block(96, 96),
        self._make_conv_block(96, 128),
        self._make_conv_block(128, 128),
        self._make_conv_block(128, 128),
        self._make_conv_block(128, 128),
        self._make_conv_block(128, 256),
        self._make_conv_block(256, 256),
        self._make_conv_block(256, 256),
        self._make_conv_block(256, 256),
    ])

    self.max_pool = nn.MaxPool2d(2, 2)
    self.fc = nn.Linear(4096, 80)

  def _make_conv_block(self, in_channels, out_channels):
      return nn.Sequential(
          nn.Conv2d(in_channels, out_channels, kernel_size=3, stride=1, padding=1),
          nn.BatchNorm2d(out_channels),
          nn.ReLU(inplace=True)
      )


  def forward(self, x):
    x = self.relu(self.bn1(self.conv1(x)))

    i = 0
    for block in self.conv_blocks:
      x = block(x)
      if i%4 == 3:
        x = self.max_pool(x)
      i+=1

    x = torch.flatten(x, 1)  # flatten except batch dimension
    x = self.fc(x)
    return x

In [11]:
def train_one_epoch(model,optim,data,loss_fn,all_labels_ofThisEpoch_train,all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_train):
  model.train()  # Set the model to training mode
  batchTruePreds = 0
  batchLoss = 0
  for batch_indx, (images, labels) in enumerate(data):
    outputs = model(images.to(device))
    loss = loss_fn(outputs, labels.to(device))

    loss.backward()
# freezing the first 80 neurons of the fc layer
    # with torch.no_grad():
    #   model.fc.weight.grad[:79, :].zero_()
    #   model.fc.bias.grad[:79].zero_()

    optim.step()
    optim.zero_grad()  # Zero the parameter gradients
    batchLoss += loss

    _, predicted = torch.max(outputs, 1)
    all_labels_ofThisEpoch_train.extend(labels.cpu().numpy())
    all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_train.extend(predicted.cpu().numpy())

    batchTruePreds += len(labels.cpu().numpy()[labels.cpu().numpy() == predicted.cpu().numpy()])


    print(f"Train-Epoch {cc}:Loss of batch {batch_indx} is {loss}")

  print("Train-Average loss of epoch : ",batchLoss/(len(data.dataset)//batch_size))
  return batchTruePreds,batchLoss,all_labels_ofThisEpoch_train,all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_train
In [12]:
def test_one_epoch(model,data,loss_fn,all_labels,all_predictions):
  model.eval()  # Set the model to testing mode
  batchLoss = 0
  batchTruePreds = 0
  with torch.no_grad():
    for batch_indx, (images, labels) in enumerate(data):
      outputs = model(images.to(device))
      loss = loss_fn(outputs, labels.to(device))
      batchLoss += loss

      _, predicted = torch.max(outputs, 1)

      all_labels.extend(labels.cpu().numpy())
      all_predictions.extend(predicted.cpu().numpy())

      batchTruePreds += len(labels.cpu().numpy()[labels.cpu().numpy() == predicted.cpu().numpy()])
      print(f"Test-Epoch {cc}:Loss of batch {batch_indx} is {loss}")

    print("Test-Average loss of epoch : ",batchLoss/(len(data.dataset)//batch_size))

    return batchTruePreds,batchLoss,all_labels,all_predictions

from utils import custom_plot_training_stats

acc_history = {'train':[],'test':[]}
loss_history = {'train':[],'test':[]}

model.to(device)

optimizer = optimizer = optim.RMSprop(model.parameters(), lr=0.00001, momentum=0.9, eps=1e-8)


epoch = 14
for cc in range(epoch):
  # train - loop
  trainingBatchTruePreds,trainingBatchLoss,all_labels_ofThisEpoch_train,all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_train = train_one_epoch(model,optimizer,A_train_dl,criterion,[],[])

  plotName = f"trainingEpoch{cc}"
  print(plotName)
  plot_conf(all_labels_ofThisEpoch_train, all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_train, 'Training ConfMat', 'Phase1TrainingDir',plotName)

  trainingEpochAccuracy = trainingBatchTruePreds/((len(A_train_dl.dataset)//batch_size)*batch_size)
  trainingEpochLoss = trainingBatchLoss/(len(A_train_dl.dataset)//batch_size)
  acc_history["train"].append(trainingEpochAccuracy)
  loss_history["train"].append(trainingEpochLoss)
  print(trainingEpochAccuracy,trainingEpochLoss)

  # test - loop

  testBatchTruePreds,testBatchLoss,all_labels_ofThisEpoch_test,all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_test = test_one_epoch(model,A_test_dl,criterion,[],[])

  plotName = f"testingEpoch{cc}"
  plot_conf(all_labels_ofThisEpoch_test, all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_test, 'Testing ConfMat', 'Phase1TestingDir',plotName)
  testingEpochAccuracy = testBatchTruePreds/((len(A_test_dl.dataset)//batch_size)*batch_size)
  testingEpochLoss = testBatchLoss/(len(A_test_dl.dataset)//batch_size)
  acc_history["test"].append(testingEpochAccuracy)
  loss_history["test"].append(testingEpochLoss)
  print(testingEpochAccuracy,testingEpochLoss)

loss_history["train"] = [x.detach().cpu() for x in loss_history["train"]]
loss_history["test"] = [x.detach().cpu() for x in loss_history["test"]]

print("asdasd")
custom_plot_training_stats(acc_history,loss_history,['train','test'],title="Phase 1 Curves",dir="Phase1Curves",name="PhaseOneCurves")

class MyModelP2(nn.Module):
  def __init__(self,original_model):
    super().__init__()
    self.conv1 = original_model.conv1
    self.bn1 = original_model.bn1
    self.relu = original_model.relu
    self.conv_blocks = original_model.conv_blocks

    self.max_pool = original_model.max_pool
    self.fc = nn.Linear(original_model.fc.in_features, original_model.fc.out_features + 20)

    with torch.no_grad():
        self.fc.weight[:original_model.fc.out_features] = original_model.fc.weight
        self.fc.bias[:original_model.fc.out_features] = original_model.fc.bias


  def forward(self, x):
    x = self.relu(self.bn1(self.conv1(x)))

    i = 0
    for block in self.conv_blocks:
      x = block(x)
      if i%4 == 3:
        x = self.max_pool(x)
      i+=1

    x = torch.flatten(x, 1)  # flatten except batch dimension
    x = self.fc(x)
    return x

from utils import custom_plot_training_stats

acc_history = {'train':[],'test':[]}
loss_history = {'train':[],'test':[]}

model22.to(device)

optimizer = optimizer = optim.RMSprop(model22.parameters(), lr=0.00001, momentum=0.9, eps=1e-8)


epoch = 10
for cc in range(epoch):
  # train - loop
  trainingBatchTruePreds,trainingBatchLoss,all_labels_ofThisEpoch_train,all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_train = train_one_epoch(model22,optimizer,B_train_dl,criterion,[],[])

  plotName = f"trainingEpoch{cc}"
  print(plotName)
  plot_conf(all_labels_ofThisEpoch_train, all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_train, 'Training ConfMat', 'Phase22TrainingDir',plotName)

  trainingEpochAccuracy = trainingBatchTruePreds/((len(B_train_dl.dataset)//batch_size)*batch_size)
  trainingEpochLoss = trainingBatchLoss/(len(B_train_dl.dataset)//batch_size)
  acc_history["train"].append(trainingEpochAccuracy)
  loss_history["train"].append(trainingEpochLoss)
  print(trainingEpochAccuracy,trainingEpochLoss)

  # test - loop

  testBatchTruePreds,testBatchLoss,all_labels_ofThisEpoch_test,all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_test = test_one_epoch(model22,test_all,criterion,[],[])

  plotName = f"testingEpoch{cc}"
  plot_conf(all_labels_ofThisEpoch_test, all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_test, 'Testing ConfMat', 'Phase22TestingAllDir',plotName)
  testingEpochAccuracy = testBatchTruePreds/((len(test_all.dataset)//batch_size)*batch_size)
  testingEpochLoss = testBatchLoss/(len(test_all.dataset)//batch_size)
  acc_history["test"].append(testingEpochAccuracy)
  loss_history["test"].append(testingEpochLoss)
  print(testingEpochAccuracy,testingEpochLoss)

loss_history["train"] = [x.detach().cpu() for x in loss_history["train"]]
loss_history["test"] = [x.detach().cpu() for x in loss_history["test"]]

custom_plot_training_stats(acc_history,loss_history,['train','test'],title="Phase 22 Curves",dir="Phase22CurvesAll",name="Curves")

  (bn1): BatchNorm2d(64, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
  (relu): ReLU(inplace=True)
  (conv_blocks): ModuleList(
    (0-3): 4 x Sequential(
      (0): Conv2d(64, 64, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(64, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (4): Sequential(
      (0): Conv2d(64, 96, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(96, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (5-7): 3 x Sequential(
      (0): Conv2d(96, 96, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(96, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (8): Sequential(
      (0): Conv2d(96, 128, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(128, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (9-11): 3 x Sequential(
      (0): Conv2d(128, 128, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(128, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (12): Sequential(
      (0): Conv2d(128, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
    (13-15): 3 x Sequential(
      (0): Conv2d(256, 256, kernel_size=(3, 3), stride=(1, 1), padding=(1, 1))
      (1): BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)
      (2): ReLU(inplace=True)
    )
  )
  (max_pool): MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2, padding=0, dilation=1, ceil_mode=False)
  (fc): Linear(in_features=4096, out_features=100, bias=True)
)

from utils import custom_plot_training_stats

acc_history = {'train':[],'test':[]}
loss_history = {'train':[],'test':[]}

model23.to(device)

optimizer = optim.RMSprop(model23.parameters(), lr=0.00001, momentum=0.9, eps=1e-8)


epoch = 10
for cc in range(epoch):
  # train - loop
  trainingBatchTruePreds,trainingBatchLoss,all_labels_ofThisEpoch_train,all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_train = train_one_epoch(model23,optimizer,B_train_dl,criterion,[],[])

  plotName = f"trainingEpoch{cc}"
  print(plotName)
  plot_conf(all_labels_ofThisEpoch_train, all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_train, 'Training ConfMat', 'Phase23TrainingDir',plotName)

  trainingEpochAccuracy = trainingBatchTruePreds/((len(B_train_dl.dataset)//batch_size)*batch_size)
  trainingEpochLoss = trainingBatchLoss/(len(B_train_dl.dataset)//batch_size)
  acc_history["train"].append(trainingEpochAccuracy)
  loss_history["train"].append(trainingEpochLoss)
  print(trainingEpochAccuracy,trainingEpochLoss)

  # test - loop

  testBatchTruePreds,testBatchLoss,all_labels_ofThisEpoch_test,all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_test = test_one_epoch(model23,test_all,criterion,[],[])

  plotName = f"testingEpoch{cc}"
  plot_conf(all_labels_ofThisEpoch_test, all_predictions_ofThisEpoch_test, 'Testing ConfMat', 'Phase23TestingAllDir',plotName)
  testingEpochAccuracy = testBatchTruePreds/((len(test_all.dataset)//batch_size)*batch_size)
  testingEpochLoss = testBatchLoss/(len(test_all.dataset)//batch_size)
  acc_history["test"].append(testingEpochAccuracy)
  loss_history["test"].append(testingEpochLoss)
  print(testingEpochAccuracy,testingEpochLoss)

loss_history["train"] = [x.detach().cpu() for x in loss_history["train"]]
loss_history["test"] = [x.detach().cpu() for x in loss_history["test"]]

custom_plot_training_stats(acc_history,loss_history,['train','test'],title="Phase 23 TestAll Curves",dir="Phase23CurvesTestAll",name="Curves")
